meanings.definition: The act or process of producing printed material.
meanings.sent1: The printings of the newspaper are done early in the morning.
meanings.sent2: She watched the printings of the flyers at the local print shop.
meanings.sent3: The printings of the brochures were so colorful, they looked like a rainbow.
meanings.sent4: The printings of the posters covered every inch of the wall.
meanings.sent5: The printings of the magazine were so crisp, it felt like you could touch the images.

meanings.definition: Copies of a book, newspaper, or other printed material.
meanings.sent1: He had a collection of rare printings of classic novels.
meanings.sent2: The library had multiple printings of the same book available for borrowing.
meanings.sent3: The printings of the comic book were so popular, they sold out in minutes.
meanings.sent4: Her room was filled with printings of old newspapers from different eras.
meanings.sent5: The printings of the magazine were stacked neatly on the shelf.

meanings.definition: The number of copies of a book, newspaper, etc., that are printed at one time.
meanings.sent1: The first printings of the novel sold out within days.
meanings.sent2: The printings of the textbook were in high demand among students.
meanings.sent3: The printings of the brochure were so many, they filled the entire room.
meanings.sent4: The printings of the newspaper were distributed to every household in the neighborhood.
meanings.sent5: The printings of the flyer were so eye-catching, everyone stopped to read them.
